Die polisie in Gauteng is opsoek na verdagtes nadat twee vroue dood en ses ander beseer in 'n drive-by skietery in Melville in Johannesburg. Die voorval het in die vroeë oggendure plaasgevind, waar mense die nuwe jaar gevier het. Brig. Mathapelo Peters, 'n polisiewoordvoerder sê: "Volgens berigte het 'n BMW-SUV uit die rigting van 7de Laan gekom. “Daar was skielik net klomp skote vanaf die BMW op mense buite die kuierplek geskiet.” Onder die persone by die kuierplek was die media-persoonlikheid Ursula Chikane. Sy het op Twitter haar ervaring gedeel. It's a fucked up thing when you have to call the security companies to assist because @SAPoliceService is over-burdened. Be safe, baby. Okay. Deep fuckin breath.I'm at my sister's house now. We were inside Poppy's grooving. An amazing night. Then, shots were fired into the spot. My head counted five rapids but there could've been two before I realised that the bangs were gunfire and not fireworks. If you had/ SOSANY DOCTORS TO MELVILLE ASAP, PLEASE!!!LIVE ROUNDS FIRED. SEVEN PEOPLE DOWN @SAPoliceService not answering need doctors on site asap Die twee vroue wie dood is was tussen 30 en 40 jaar oud. Twee sake van moord en ses van poging tot moord word ondersoek. 'n Beroep word gedoen op enigeen met inligting om die polisie te kontak. We on the scene this morning where two people were killed at Poppy’s Restaurant in Melville. Crime Scene Investigators are on the scene. 6 other people have been hospitalized, two of which are critical. #Melville pic.twitter.com/96JnudPSE4 